derivation.yuyuan_name: late 19th cent.: from Latin resonat- 'resounded', from the verb resonare (see resound)

entry.tran: 发出嘹亮的声音;回响;回荡
entry.def: If something resonates, it vibrates and produces a deep, strong sound.

example.ex: The bass guitar began to thump so loudly that it resonated in my head.
example.tran: 低音电吉他开始砰砰作响，巨大的声音一直在我的脑海里回响。

entry.def: You say that something resonates when it has a special meaning or when it is particularly important to someone.

example.ex: London is confident and alive, resonating with all the qualities of a civilised city.
example.tran: 伦敦洋溢着自信和活力，呈现出一个文明城市的所有特性。

sentences.sentence: "The sound resonates well in this theater"
